#===========================================================================================================================
# Class Mob
#  group abstraction, acts as an interface for a collection of minds to cooperate
#  a Mob could represent a small group of monsters, ie 3 bandits robbing travellers 
#                        a large group of monsters, ie a tribe of goblins
#                        a herd, pride, or other cooperative group
#
#  Modes:
#    cooperative: Mob passes messages between component minds, which independantly choose a course of action based on
#                 internal heuristics
#    swarm: Mob sends 'orders' to minds, which then attempt to exetcute the orders. An order represents a request, and the
#           mob acts as a coordinator (a kind of meta-mind)
#  Interface
#    
#
#===========================================================================================================================


